Quotation[177] = "If you are going to have less things, they have to be great things. &#x2015;John Maeda"; 
Quotation[178] = "We aren&#039;t designing photocopies of web pages, we&#039;re designing web pages. &#x2015;Andy Clarke"; 
Quotation[179] = "Stare. It is the way to educate your eye, and more. Stare, pry, listen, eavesdrop. Die knowing something. You are not here long. &#x2015;Walker Evans"; 
Quotation[180] = "I rarely agree with what clients ask me to do. &#x2015;Ross Lovegrove"; 
Quotation[181] = "A pessimist sees the difficulty in every opportunity; an optimist sees the opportunity in every difficulty. &#x2015;Winston Churchill"; 
Quotation[182] = "Less is more. &#x2015;Ludwig Mies van der Rohe"; 
Quotation[183] = "It&#039;s the little details that are vital. Little things make big things happen. &#x2015;Coach John Wooden"; 
Quotation[184] = "Just because your ad looks good is no insurance that it will get looked at. How many people do you know who are impeccably groomed… but dull? &#x2015;Bill Bernbach"; 
Quotation[185] = "People always ask, &#034;What do you think of my site?&#034; I want to say back to them, &#034;Who cares what I think. Does it meet your site requirements? Has it been tested? Has each requirement been validated? Are your site guidelines being adhered to?&#034; &#x2015;Kim Krause"; 
Quotation[186] = "If you do good work for good clients, it will lead to other good work for other good clients. If you do bad work for bad clients, it will lead to other bad work for other bad clients. &#x2015;Michael Bierut"; 
Quotation[187] = "Marketing without design is lifeless, and design without marketing is mute. &#x2015;Von R. Glitschka"; 
Quotation[188] = "Chances are, unless I&#039;m a designer, I don&#039;t know what I want. All I know is I want something functional that looks good, is comparable with my competitors, and features constant colour schemes for branding. I&#039;ll look at other designs that have already been created and ask for something similar. Hence, it is important that you can take the information I give and help me visualize what it is you think I want. &#x2015;Aditya Mahesh"; 
Quotation[189] = "Minimalism is not a lack of something. It&#039;s simply the perfect amount of something. &#x2015;Nicholas Burroughs"; 
Quotation[190] = "A picture is worth a thousand dollars. &#x2015;Marty Neumeier"; 
Quotation[191] = "Experience has shown that our best customers are ones who have as much respect for our time as we have for theirs. &#x2015;Alex King"; 
Quotation[192] = "If I do my job well, the identity program will also clean up the image of the company, position it as being contemporary and keep it from ever looking dated. &#x2015;Saul Bass"; 
Quotation[193] = "Suppose I showed you two rooms where in one a group of programmers was developing a program to monitor a heart patient and keep him alive until the doctors arrive if something goes wrong and in the other a group of street people was using Microsoft Word to write letters to their parole officers. You would not be able to tell the rooms apart. &#x2015;Richard P. Gabriel"; 
Quotation[194] = "What&#039;s the hardest thing to communicate? The hardest thing is to communicate. &#x2015;Michael Cina"; 
Quotation[195] = "Truly elegant design incorporates top-notch functionality into a simple, uncluttered form. &#x2015;David Lewis"; 
Quotation[196] = "If it were easy to nut out tricky design problems, I might be out of a job. But it&#039;s also true that the cleverness in most lateral design doesn&#039;t come from blindly grinding away at the same concept. When you&#039;re dealing with ideas, it&#039;s rarely a matter of simply putting in more time working. Five minutes can be much more fruitful than five hours. &#x2015;Rob Morris"; 
Quotation[197] = "If design isn&#039;t profitable, then it&#039;s art. &#x2015;Henrik Fiskar"; 
Quotation[198] = "A mystery is the most stimulating force in unleashing the imagination. &#x2015;Zuzana Licko and Rudy VanderLans"; 
Quotation[199] = "There is an unmistakeable difference between a bag of rabbit parts and a rabbit. &#x2015;Ryan Nance"; 
Quotation[200] = "There is no such thing as simple. Simple is hard. &#x2015;Martin Scorsese"; 
Quotation[201] = "What garlic is to food, insanity is to art. &#x2015;Unknown"; 
Quotation[202] = "All projects are different, but you have treat each one with care. Sometimes you get to build a luxury yacht; other times, it&#039;ll be a rowboat. You still have to make sure the thing doesn&#039;t spring a leak. &#x2015;Stefan G. Bucher"; 
Quotation[203] = "Never half-ass two things. Whole-ass one thing. &#x2015;Ron Swanson"; 
Quotation[204] = "The real issue is not talent as an independent element, but talent in relationship to will, desire, and persistence. Talent without these things vanishes and even modest talent with those characteristics grows. &#x2015;Milton Glaser"; 
Quotation[205] = "Clients are the difference between design and art. &#x2015;Michael Bierut"; 
Quotation[206] = "Where you innovate, how you innovate, and what you innovate are design problems. &#x2015;Tim Brown"; 
Quotation[207] = "Opportunity is missed by people because it is dressed in overalls and looks like work. &#x2015;Thomas Edison"; 
Quotation[208] = "Don&#039;t let your design resist your readers. Don&#039;t let it stand in the way of what they want to do&#058; read. &#x2015;Steve Krug"; 
Quotation[209] = "Be regular and orderly in your life like a bourgeois, so that you may be violent and original in your work. &#x2015;Gustave Flaubert"; 
Quotation[210] = "Redesigning somebody else&#039;s product is always a tricky business. You don&#039;t know why they made the decisions they made. You don&#039;t have the data they have. &#x2015;Lukas Mathis"; 
Quotation[211] = "No one is finally dead until the ripples they cause in the world die away, until the clock wound up winds down, until the wine she made has finished its ferment, until the crop they planted is harvested. The span of someone&#039;s life is only the core of their actual existence. &#x2015;Terry Pratchett"; 
Quotation[212] = "Stop. I&#039;m not going to take any more input until I&#039;ve made something with what I got. &#x2015;Merlin Mann"; 
Quotation[213] = "Here is one of the few effective keys to the design problem — the ability of the designer to recognize as many of the constraints as possible — his willingness and enthusiasm for working within these constraints. Constraints of price, of size, of strength, of balance, of surface, of time and so forth. &#x2015;Charles Eames"; 
Quotation[214] = "Defamiliarize the ordinary. &#x2015;Paul Rand"; 
Quotation[215] = "The process is really just Iterate, Iterate, Iterate. &#x2015;Chris Clark"; 
Quotation[216] = "Worry is essentially a misuse of imagination. &#x2015;Alex Osborn"; 
Quotation[217] = "The secret to our enduring brand lies in delivering an experience rather than just a collection of products and services. &#x2015;Harley-Davidson Annual Report"; 
Quotation[218] = "Design is a process for making things right, for shaping what people need. &#x2015;Ralph Caplan"; 
Quotation[219] = "Communication that doesn&#039;t take a chance doesn&#039;t stand a chance. &#x2015;Carlos Segura"; 
Quotation[220] = "A work of art is one of mystery, the one extreme magic; everything else is either arithmetic or biology. &#x2015;Truman Capote"; 
Quotation[221] = "You are what you are seen to be. &#x2015;Erik Spiekermann"; 
Quotation[222] = "Man up, admit it isn&#039;t good enough, and fix it now. &#x2015;Robert Nealan"; 
Quotation[223] = "Design trends online change more often than the wind, and slightly less often than my socks. &#x2015;Suleiman Leadbitter"; 
Quotation[224] = "We need to shift from designing applications to designing implications. &#x2015;Anthony Dunne & Fiona Raby"; 
Quotation[225] = "To create great work, here&#039;s how you must spend your time&#058; 1% Inspiration 9% Perspiration 90% Justification &#x2015;George Lois"; 
Quotation[226] = "We are so busying measuring public opinion that we forget we can mold it. We are so busy listening to statistics we forget we can create them. &#x2015;Bill Bernbach"; 
Quotation[227] = "However beautiful the strategy, you should occasionally look at the results. &#x2015;Winston Churchill"; 
Quotation[228] = "We are only three decades into one of the most important revolutions the world has ever seen. In design development terms, that is a mere blink. &#x2015;Rachel Hinman"; 
Quotation[229] = "Creativity is magical, but is not magic. &#x2015;Charles Limb"; 
Quotation[230] = "Great ideas can be found in every leaf, in every tree, in every blade of grass. Oh, no, wait… I was thinking of chlorophyll. &#x2015;Jim Olen"; 
Quotation[231] = "… try to absorb what is useful, discard what is useless, and add what is essentially your own. &#x2015;Bruce Lee"; 
Quotation[232] = "Any product that needs a manual to work is broken. &#x2015;Elon Musk"; 
Quotation[233] = "We&#039;re all naturally curious when we&#039;re eight years old. But as most people get older, they become less and less curious, so they ask other people to be curious for them. That&#039;s what I do for a living. &#x2015;Ron Miriello"; 
Quotation[234] = "We read best what we read most. &#x2015;Zuzana Licko"; 
Quotation[235] = "Making good design is easy. It&#039;s polishing the half-assed stuff that takes time. &#x2015;Stefan G. Bucher"; 
Quotation[236] = "The strategy in communications is not to sell the 1/4?-inch drill bit, but the 1/4?-inch hole. &#x2015;Robert Louey"; 
Quotation[237] = "To create anything–whether a short story or a magazine profile or a film or a sitcom–is to believe, if only momentarily, you are capable of magic. &#x2015;Tom Bissel"; 
Quotation[238] = "If you do what you always did, you will get what you always got. &#x2015;Albert Einstein"; 
Quotation[239] = "Be curious. Read widely. Try new things. I think a lot of what people call intelligence boils down to curiosity. &#x2015;Aaron Schwartz"; 
Quotation[240] = "The majority of iteration should be done in the privacy of your own head. &#x2015;Steven Walker"; 
Quotation[241] = "Whenever I have an idea I write it down, even if it&#039;s not a very good idea. Sometimes the bad ideas will lead to better ones. &#x2015;Steven Snell"; 
Quotation[242] = "You have to finish things — that&#039;s what you learn from, you learn by finishing things. &#x2015;Neil Gaiman"; 
Quotation[243] = "Art has to move you and design does not, unless it&#039;s a good design for a bus. &#x2015;David Hockney"; 
Quotation[244] = "There&#039;s no shortcut for greatness. &#x2015;Yasin Japardi"; 
Quotation[245] = "The thing that&#039;s so wonderful about using beautiful, appropriate tools is that they become an extension of you, your body, you fingertips, and your mind. They get out of the way and let you directly interact with the problem you are solving. Everyone&#039;s tried to remove a screw without a screwdriver; a task quickly becomes impossible that otherwise would be trivial. &#x2015;Luke Crawford"; 
Quotation[246] = "Today&#039;s designers and illustrators are synthesizing the best elements from past eras of graphic design to create a new visual language with a reduced and rational approach. &#x2015;R. Klanten, H. Hellige"; 
Quotation[247] = "Best thing about creating something is that it starts living it&#039;s own life. &#x2015;Hristo Panayotov"; 
Quotation[248] = "The most effective way to make a design usable is to make it interesting enough that people want to use it. &#x2015;Bryan Grezeszak"; 
Quotation[249] = "To see takes time. &#x2015;Georgia O&#039;Keeffe"; 
Quotation[250] = "I&#039;m sure there are fine artists out there who keep the audience in mind when they work. But it&#039;s not the accepted trajectory of the profession. Conversely, it&#039;s very clear in design that what we do needs to be seen an understood by an audience. &#x2015;Stefan Sagmeister"; 
Quotation[251] = "I was gonna get a candy bar; the button I was supposed to push was &#034;HH&#034;, so I went to the side, I found the &#034;H&#034; button, I pushed it twice. Fuckin&#039;…potato chips came out, man, because they had an &#034;HH&#034; button for Christ&#039;s sake! You need to let me know. I&#039;m not familiar with the concept of &#034;HH&#034;. I did not learn my AA-BB-CC&#039;s. God god, dammit dammit. &#x2015;Mitch Hedberg"; 
Quotation[252] = "Like all forms of design, visual design is about problem solving, not about personal preference or unsupported opinion. &#x2015;Bob Baxley"; 
Quotation[253] = "Only show work you like, or you&#039;ll end up being hired to do things you don&#039;t like. &#x2015;Victoria Pater"; 
Quotation[254] = "If you can&#039;t draw as well as someone, or use the software as well, or if you do not have as much money to buy supplies, or if you do not have access to the tools they have, beat them by being more thoughtful. Thoughtfulness is free and burns on time and empathy. &#x2015;Frank Chimero"; 
Quotation[255] = "I In fact choose to use a coffeemaker to boil vegetables. Why? Because if I used something else that just makes coffee, my client would ask me &#034;Can it boil vegetables?&#034; &#x2015;Joel Fisher"; 
Quotation[256] = "Designers tend to whisper, ad agencies tend to shout. &#x2015;David Stuart"; 
Quotation[257] = "I just worked hard and tried to make my thing better. &#x2015;Jesse Thorn"; 
Quotation[258] = "The aim of art is to represent not the outward appearance of things, but their inward significance. &#x2015;Aristotle"; 
Quotation[259] = "Design is crucially important. We can&#039;t have advances in technology any longer, unless design is integrated from the very start. &#x2015;John Underkoffler"; 
Quotation[260] = "Here&#039;s the world&#039;s worst idea for a movie&#058; Titanic. It did okay at the box office. &#x2015;Scott Adams"; 
Quotation[261] = "Find the simple story in the product, and present it in an articulate and intelligent, persuasive way. &#x2015;Bill Bernbach"; 
Quotation[262] = "Easy is not to be underestimated. Easy taps the pool of talent and ideas out there that were turned off by hard. &#x2015;Chris Anderson"; 
Quotation[263] = "A good portfolio will get you an interview. A good attitude will get you a job. &#x2015;Marty Amsler"; 
Quotation[264] = "We can&#039;t solve problems by using the same kind of thinking we used when we created them. &#x2015;Albert Einstein"; 
Quotation[265] = "Design is as much an act of spacing as an act of marking. &#x2015;Ellen Lupton"; 
Quotation[266] = "Never do anything yourself that you can hire someone else to do, especially if they can do it better. &#x2015;Bill Bernback"; 
Quotation[267] = "In the design process, my gut instinct is my best critic. I just wish I would always listen to it! &#x2015;Bryan Tamayo"; 
Quotation[268] = "Propaganda supersedes fact, truth and common sense in all cases. &#x2015;P.S.C. Trier"; 
Quotation[269] = "Socrates said, &#034;Know thyself.&#034; I say, &#034;Know thy users.&#034; And guess what? They don&#039;t think like you do. &#x2015;Joshua Brewer"; 
Quotation[270] = "We have a strategic plan. It&#039;s called doing things. &#x2015;Herb Kelleher"; 
Quotation[271] = "Objects and their manufacture are inseparable, you understand a product if you understand how it&#039;s made. &#x2015;Jonathan Ive"; 
Quotation[272] = "If you can&#039;t solve a problem, it&#039;s because you&#039;re playing by the rules. &#x2015;Paul Arden"; 
Quotation[273] = "However, I&#039;ve always been more concerned with users. Programmers do their work but once, while users are saddled with it ever thereafter. &#x2015;Jef Raskin"; 
Quotation[274] = "I know the price of success&#058; dedication, hard work & an unremitting devotion to the things you want to see happen. &#x2015;Frank Lloyd Wright"; 
Quotation[275] = "Clients don&#039;t understand their success is reliant on standing out, not fitting in. &#x2015;Don Draper"; 
Quotation[276] = "Perfect typography is certainly the most elusive of all arts. Sculpture in stone alone comes near it in obstinacy. &#x2015;Jan Tschichold"; 
Quotation[277] = "Every designers&#039; dirty little secret is that they copy other designers&#039; work. They see work they like, and they imitate it. Rather cheekily, they call this inspiration. &#x2015;Aaron Russell"; 
Quotation[278] = "When I am down, [I am] not good at any work, including design work. &#x2015;Stefan Sagmeister"; 
Quotation[279] = "More designers should share space, share resources. Sort of an upscale communism. &#x2015;April Greiman"; 
Quotation[280] = "Do right. &#x2015;Jeffrey Brown"; 
Quotation[281] = "Preparation gives birth to self-confidence. &#x2015;Denise Harman"; 
Quotation[282] = "A good design can feel like something you have always been waiting for without knowing. &#x2015;Paul Huizinga"; 
Quotation[283] = "Any intelligent fool can make things bigger, more complex, and more violent. It takes a touch of genius – and a lot of courage – to move in the opposite direction. &#x2015;Albert Einstein"; 
Quotation[284] = "Don&#039;t try and reinvent the wheel – just work on making it better than anyone else. &#x2015;David A. Stuebe"; 
Quotation[285] = "Now that we can do anything, what should we do? &#x2015;Bill Buxton"; 
Quotation[286] = "Almost everything – all external expectations, all pride, all fear of embarrassment or failure – these things just fall away in the face of death, leaving only what is truly important. &#x2015;Steve Jobs"; 
Quotation[287] = "Descriptions are like skirts, they should be long enough to cover the subject, but short enough to keep things interesting. &#x2015;Gidsy.com"; 
Quotation[288] = "It&#039;s art if it can&#039;t be explained. It&#039;s fashion if no one asks for an explanation. It&#039;s design if it doesn&#039;t need explanation. &#x2015;Wouter Stokkel"; 
Quotation[289] = "The typeface doesn&#039;t really matter, as long as the text is good. &#x2015;John Maeda"; 
Quotation[290] = "Babe Ruth was a Home Run king but he was also a strike out king. Always go for the fences, even if it means some designs strike out with clients. That&#039;s the only way to hit a home run. &#x2015;Alex Zevallos"; 
Quotation[291] = "Usage is like oxygen for ideas. &#x2015;Matt Mullenweg"; 
Quotation[292] = "Ability proceeds from a fusion of skills, knowledge, understanding and imagination, consolidated by experience. &#x2015;Jonathan Rez"; 
Quotation[293] = "Curiosity about life in all of its aspects, I think, is still the secret of great creative people. &#x2015;Leo Burnett"; 
Quotation[294] = "Computer design is quite often merely bad design done on a computer. &#x2015;Mike Hicks"; 
Quotation[295] = "Computers are to design as microwaves are to cooking. &#x2015;Milton Glaser"; 
Quotation[296] = "Don&#039;t stare at a blank page for too long, be bold, and make the first incisive stroke. The rest will come naturally. &#x2015;James Kingman"; 
Quotation[297] = "I didn&#039;t get into design to be an artist. To me, an artist creates things to evoke emotion. Being a designer goes a step further than that, not only trying to evoke emotion but trying to make a reaction. It is very objective-driven, and that&#039;s what makes it interesting. &#x2015;Mike Davidson"; 
Quotation[298] = "Good design means never having to say &#034;Click Here.&#034; &#x2015;Shawn Leslie"; 
Quotation[299] = "When the only tool you own is a hammer, every problem begins to resemble a nail. &#x2015;Abraham Maslow"; 
Quotation[300] = "Simplicity is the ultimate sophistication. &#x2015;Leonardo da Vinci"; 
Quotation[301] = "It&#039;s about whittling. It&#039;s about taking something and whittling and whittling and getting it sharp and perfect. Then you&#039;ve got something. &#x2015;James Victore"; 
Quotation[302] = "We are not artists or poets. We are artisans and craftsmen. Our products solve problems. They do not hang on museum walls. &#x2015;Dan Lacivita"; 
Quotation[303] = "We make the whole widget. &#x2015;Steve Jobs"; 
Quotation[304] = "At the age of six I wanted to be a cook. At seven I wanted to be Napoleon. And my ambition has been growing steadily ever since. &#x2015;Salvador Dali"; 
Quotation[305] = "Never re-invent the wheel, unless you&#039;re sure the client needn&#039;t go anywhere. &#x2015;Russell Bishop"; 
Quotation[306] = "Helvetica is like a really good friend. You go off and hang with the other fonts (the artsy, grungy, trendy, thin, fat, tall, scripty types) and even use them a little, but helvetica is always there. A nice stable friend. &#x2015;Andrew Frigo"; 
Quotation[307] = "It&#039;s all fun and games until someone breaks a link. &#x2015;Derek Vigil"; 
Quotation[308] = "An old surrealist trick was to take images that had no business being together and plopping them into the same image. Your mind wants to make associations. Design does that all the time. &#x2015;Art Chantry"; 
Quotation[309] = "No great thing is created suddenly. &#x2015;Epictetus"; 
Quotation[310] = "Graphic design has been likened to a wine glass. When we drink wine we barely notice the glass it&#039;s served in. It wouldn&#039;t be true to say that we don&#039;t care what glass we drink out of – we wouldn&#039;t choose to drink a rare vintage out of a Tupperware mug, for example – but it&#039;s the wine that matters, not the vessel it comes in. &#x2015;Adrian Shaughnessy"; 
Quotation[311] = "Without deviation from the norm progress is not possible. &#x2015;Frank Zappa"; 
Quotation[312] = "If I create from the heart, nearly everything works; if from the head, almost nothing. &#x2015;Marc Chagall"; 
Quotation[313] = "If you see a few lines of atrocious code, you can make a judgement about the programmer. By judging the programmer, you can judge his boss, and by judging his boss you can judge the company. That&#039;s the nature of fractals. &#x2015;Des Traynor"; 
Quotation[314] = "The secret to creativity is knowing how to hide your sources. &#x2015;Albert Einstein"; 
Quotation[315] = "Good design must be defined by appropriateness to audience and goals, and by its effectiveness, not by its adherence to Swiss design or the number of awards it wins. &#x2015;Drew Davies"; 
Quotation[316] = "To say a grid is limiting is to say that language is limiting, or typography is limiting. &#x2015;Ellen Lupton"; 
Quotation[317] = "Wisdom is knowing what to do next, skill is knowing how to do it, and virtue is doing it. &#x2015;David Starr"; 
Quotation[318] = "Elegance is not the abundance of simplicity. It is the absence of complexity. &#x2015;Alex White"; 
Quotation[319] = "…is innovative …makes a product useful …is aesthetic …helps a product to be understood …is unobtrusive …is honest …is durable …is thorough to the last detail …is concerned with the environment …is as little design as possible &#x2015;Dieter Rams"; 
Quotation[320] = "It has taken my entire life to understand what I already knew about creating art in 3rd grade. &#x2015;Philip Carrera"; 
Quotation[321] = "Art is an idea that has found its perfect visual expression. And design is the vehicle by which this expression is made possible. Art is a noun, and design is a noun and also a verb. Art is a product and design is a process. Design is the foundation of all the arts. &#x2015;Paul Rand"; 
Quotation[322] = "Creativity is a drug I cannot live without. &#x2015;Cecil B. DeMille"; 
Quotation[323] = "Find something you&#039;re passionate about and keep tremendously interested in it. &#x2015;Julia Child"; 
Quotation[324] = "When you do something, you should burn yourself up completely, like a good bonfire, leaving no trace of yourself. &#x2015;Shunryu Suzuki"; 
Quotation[325] = "A common mistake that people make when trying to design something completely foolproof is to underestimate the ingenuity of complete fools. &#x2015;Douglas Adams"; 
Quotation[326] = "Good design is finding a solution to a problem. Great design is finding the simplest solution to the same problem. &#x2015;Nicholas Petersen"; 
Quotation[327] = "When graphic designers got bored with the perfection offered by the newly arrived computers that could render artwork to within a tiny pixel, they rebelled by writing programmes that randomized individual letters and whole pages every time a printer processed them. A designer who didn&#039;t like what a copywriter had delivered even set that text in illegible pictograms and icons. &#x2015;Erik Spiekermann"; 
Quotation[328] = "Brand identity is too often limited to personal style. &#x2015;David A. Stuebe"; 
Quotation[329] = "Consistency is one of the most powerful usability principles&#058; when things always behave the same, users don&#039;t have to worry about what will happen. Instead, they know what will happen based on earlier experience. &#x2015;Jakob Nielsen"; 
Quotation[330] = "Most [clients] expect experience design to be a discrete activity, solving all their problems with a single functional specification or a single research study. It must be an ongoing effort, a process of continually learning about users, responding to their behaviors, and evolving the product or service. &#x2015;Dan Brown"; 
Quotation[331] = "Typography is a beautiful group of letters, not a group of beautiful letters. &#x2015;Steve Byers"; 
Quotation[332] = "The worst thing you can do to anybody trying to be creative is to demand participation in their vision. &#x2015;Chuck Klosterman"; 
Quotation[333] = "No matter how cool your interface is, it would be better if there were less of it. &#x2015;Alan Cooper"; 
Quotation[334] = "Those who say &#034;it&#039;s not personal, it&#039;s just business&#034; are lying. All business is personal, and the best business is very personal. &#x2015;Richard Lenz"; 
Quotation[335] = "It&#039;s not what you look at that matters, it&#039;s what you see. &#x2015;Henry David Thoreau"; 
Quotation[336] = "I don&#039;t want something special. I want something beautifully plain. &#x2015;Anne Lamott"; 
Quotation[337] = "Designers are meant to be loved, not to be understood. &#x2015;Fabien Barral"; 
Quotation[338] = "Every practice has a set of rules which governs it. Mastery occurs with the realization of these rules. Innovation occurs at the point of intelligent and creative rebellion against them. &#x2015;Fiel Valdez"; 
Quotation[339] = "I recently saw another demonstration of graphic design&#039;s ubiquity. Someone had taken a series of photographs of busy streets and then painstakingly removed all the logos, symbols, signs, colours, street names and road markings. In other words, they had removed all the graphic design from these photographs. The results were staggering. A world without graphic design is an unrecognizable world — more alien than all but the most extreme sci-fi imaginings. &#x2015;Adrian Shaughnessy"; 
Quotation[340] = "Here&#039;s to the crazy ones. The misfits. The rebels. The troublemakers. The round pegs in the square holes.?The ones who see things differently. They&#039;re not fond of rules. And they have no respect for the status quo. You can praise them, disagree with them, quote them, disbelieve them, glorify or vilify them. ?About the only thing you can&#039;t do is ignore them. Because they change things. They invent. They imagine. They heal. They explore. They create. They inspire. They push the human race forward.?Maybe they have to be crazy.?How else can you stare at an empty canvas and see a work of art? Or sit in silence and hear a song that&#039;s never been written? Or gaze at a red planet and see a laboratory on wheels?? While some see them as the crazy ones, we see genius. Because the people who are crazy enough to think they can change the world, are the ones who do. &#x2015;Apple Commercial"; 
Quotation[341] = "It is easier to talk than to listen. Pay attention to your clients, your users, your readers, and your friends. Your design will get better as you listen to other people. &#x2015;Ellen Lupton"; 
Quotation[342] = "There are no bad ideas, just bad decisions. &#x2015;Jacob Cass"; 
Quotation[343] = "As a designer, I find it difficult not to judge a book by its cover. &#x2015;Jordan Manigo"; 
Quotation[344] = "In design man becomes what he is. Animals have language and perception as well, but they do not design. &#x2015;Otl Aicher"; 
Quotation[345] = "Programming today is a race between software engineers striving to build bigger and better idiot-proof programs, and the universe trying to build bigger and better idiots. So far, the universe is winning. &#x2015;Rick Cook"; 
Quotation[346] = "Practice safe design&#058; Use a concept. &#x2015;Petrula Vrontikis"; 
Quotation[347] = "Every child is an artist. The challenge is to remain an artist after you grow up. &#x2015;Pablo Picasso"; 
Quotation[348] = "It&#039;s strange, I&#039;ve seen colours at times that when I&#039;ve gone back to check on them, they&#039;ve vanished… &#x2015;William Percy Weston"; 
Quotation[349] = "History has remembered the kings and warriors, because they destroyed; art has remembered the people, because they created. &#x2015;William Morris"; 
Quotation[350] = "For every new feature we add, we take an old one out. A lot of big sites don&#039;t do that, and it&#039;s a problem. Twitter started as a beautifully simple product, but it&#039;s now going the same route as Facebook. The drive to innovate can overencumber and destroy a product. &#x2015;David Karp"; 
Quotation[351] = "Design is the contrast of the core of limitations therefore there are no boundaries. It is simply an interpretation of creativity. &#x2015;Jenaiha Woods"; 
Quotation[352] = "I really like looking at design and thinking&#058; that attention to detail must have taken absolutely ages. &#x2015;Si Scott"; 
Quotation[353] = "What we got here is… failure to communicate. &#x2015;Cool Hand Luke"; 
Quotation[354] = "Offend nobody, design for somebody. &#x2015;Paul Boag"; 
Quotation[355] = "Smart people are attracted to stories, not feature lists. &#x2015;Johnnie Manzari"; 
Quotation[356] = "Design is so critical it should be on the agenda of every meeting in every single department. &#x2015;Tom Peters"; 
Quotation[357] = "Don&#039;t mistake legibility for communication. &#x2015;David Carson"; 
Quotation[358] = "Designing for clients that don&#039;t appreciate the value of design is like buying new tires for a rental car. &#x2015;Joel Fisher"; 
Quotation[359] = "Web design has a bad reputation for being stylistically trendy and same-looking. Some guy does a parallax scrolling site, and now your boss wants you to add that to your corporate PR website for some reason. Glossy buttons, Gaussian Noise, linen texture, new things that look fake-old, then back to minimalism and flat colors as a reaction to the glossy noisy textured fake-old stuff. &#x2015;Jonas Downey"; 
Quotation[360] = "One of the most significant differences between graphic designers and other visual artists is our unhinged love of typography. &#x2015;Greg Breeding"; 
Quotation[361] = "A logo doesn&#039;t sell, it identifies. A logo derives its meaning from the quality of the thing it symbolizes, not the other way around. A logo is less important than the product it signifies; what it means is more important than what it looks like. &#x2015;Paul Rand"; 
Quotation[362] = "Observation and imitation are so often the steps to creative maturation. An insightful person can turn these into innovation. &#x2015;Pete Episcopo"; 
Quotation[363] = "He who cannot draw on three thousand years is living from hand to mouth. &#x2015;Johann Wolfgang von Goethe"; 
Quotation[364] = "When you make something no one hates, no one loves it. &#x2015;Tibor Kalman"; 
Quotation[365] = "Things you think are obvious often aren&#039;t, text you thought explained something doesn&#039;t even get read, and generally speaking users do things they weren&#039;t supposed to do. Even if the only user testing you ever do is asking some friends to use a site while you observe them, you&#039;ll already be better for it. &#x2015;Collis Ta&#039;eed"; 
Quotation[366] = "The way to &#034;get your name out there&#034; is to establish a pattern of excellent work and a reputation for integrity over several years. &#x2015;Andy Rutledge"; 
Quotation[367] = "Decoration is just make-up for the wrinkles of the idea. &#x2015;Thomas Manss"; 
Quotation[368] = "The best ideas come as jokes. Make your thinking as funny as possible. &#x2015;David Ogilvy"; 
Quotation[369] = "The design business continues to navel gaze. Designers are still designing for other designers rather than working to convince the business world of the importance of design in our everyday lives. &#x2015;Joe Duffy"; 
Quotation[370] = "Sometimes you have to keep ideas for decades before they have any use. &#x2015;Marc English"; 
Quotation[371] = "I don&#039;t think that all people read in the same way. Today, entire generations are growing up watching MTV and playing video games and it is safe to assume that these people have a high degree of visual sophistication. and are not easily discouraged by a lens straightforward or ambiguous typography. On the contrary, they are attracted and enticed to read something because of visual richness. &#x2015;Ruby Vanderlans"; 
Quotation[372] = "Be a first rate version of yourself, not a second rate version of someone else. &#x2015;Judy Garland"; 
Quotation[373] = "Good design is partially creativity and innovation, but primarily knowledge and awareness. &#x2015;Chuck Green"; 
Quotation[374] = "Never show fools unfinished work. &#x2015;Michael Schrage"; 
Quotation[375] = "Teaching peers is one of the best ways to develop mastery. &#x2015;Jeff Atwood"; 
Quotation[376] = "Whoever tells the best story wins. &#x2015;Annette Simmons"; 
Quotation[377] = "Inspiration is perishable. &#x2015;37 Signals"; 
Quotation[378] = "If the users can&#039;t find it, the function&#039;s not there. &#x2015;Human Factors International"; 
Quotation[379] = "Artists are natural marketers for everyone but themselves. &#x2015;Oren Sherman"; 
Quotation[380] = "When Einstein realized, &#034;Dear me, this universe with its wonders all adds up to E=mc2?,&#034; he did not stop to think whether this concept would sell better set in Futura or Antikva. &#x2015;Kari Piippo"; 
Quotation[381] = "Inspired interiors indubitably involve ingenious imitations of inspired interiors. &#x2015;Ana Cummings"; 
Quotation[382] = "Thirty spokes meet in the hub, but the empty space between them is the essence of the wheel. Pots are formed from clay, but the empty space within it is the essence of the pot. Walls with windows and doors form the house, but the empty space within it is the essence of the home. &#x2015;Lao Tse"; 
Quotation[383] = "Begin with the end in mind. &#x2015;Lana Rigsby"; 
Quotation[384] = "When I design, I don&#039;t consider the technical or commercial parameters so much as the desire for a dream that humans have attempted to project onto an object. &#x2015;Philippe Starck"; 
Quotation[385] = "Do what you love and tomorrow will pay the rent. &#x2015;Felix Sockwell"; 
Quotation[386] = "Perfection is achieved, not when there is nothing more to add, but when there is nothing left to take away. &#x2015;Antoine de Saint Exupéry"; 
Quotation[387] = "Business owners need to realize that their design is a reflection of their business even if it is not intentional. If you don&#039;t care about your design then your design is telling people that you don&#039;t care about your business. &#x2015;Marco Suarez"; 
Quotation[388] = "Everything was just a wild guess. And it takes a while to get confident that you&#039;re guessing pretty good. &#x2015;Jerry Seinfeld"; 
Quotation[389] = "I try and be as stupid as possible regarding my profession, which means I try to look at as few design magazines as possible. &#x2015;Ettore Sottsass"; 
Quotation[390] = "I shall sing that first line twice, and perhaps if I sing it very quickly, I shall find myself singing the third and fourth lines before I have time to think of them, and that will be a Good Song. &#x2015;Winnie The Pooh"; 
Quotation[391] = "Wondering is the seed of genius. &#x2015;William Mocca"; 
Quotation[392] = "The challenge is for the graphic designer to turn data into information and information into messages of meaning. &#x2015;Katherine McCoy"; 
Quotation[393] = "Show me someone who has done something worthwhile, and I&#039;ll show you someone who has overcome adversity. &#x2015;Lou Holtz"; 
Quotation[394] = "A user interface is like a joke. If you have to explain it, it&#039;s not that good. &#x2015;Martin LeBlanc"; 
Quotation[395] = "When in doubt, use Caslon. &#x2015;William Caslon"; 
Quotation[396] = "Once the problem was stated, its solution came to me in a flash. &#x2015;Anton Fokker"; 
Quotation[397] = "Designers think everything done by someone else is awful, and that they could do it better themselves, which explains why I designed my own living room carpet, I suppose. &#x2015;Chris Bangle"; 
Quotation[398] = "A healthy creative process should be able to give a coherent rationale to a client as to why you designed what you designed. &#x2015;Von Glitschka"; 
Quotation[399] = "The only true happiness comes from squandering ourselves for a purpose. &#x2015;John Mason Brown"; 
Quotation[400] = "I am always doing that which I can not do, in order that I may learn how to do it. &#x2015;Pablo Picasso"; 
Quotation[401] = "Every act of creation is first an act of destruction. &#x2015;Pablo Picasso"; 
Quotation[402] = "Bad design is smoke, while good design is a mirror. &#x2015;Juan-Carlos Fernandez"; 
Quotation[403] = "Your imagination is the hood ornament on the car of creativity. &#x2015;Gary Busey"; 
Quotation[404] = "The most innovative designers consciously reject the standard option box and cultivate an appetite for thinking wrong. &#x2015;Marty Neumeier"; 
Quotation[405] = "A designer is an emerging synthesis of artist, inventor, mechanic, objective economist and evolutio­nary strategist. &#x2015;Buckminster Fuller"; 
Quotation[406] = "A perfect implementation of the wrong specification is worthless. By the same principle a beautifully crafted library with no documentation is also damn near worthless. If your software solves the wrong problem or nobody can figure out how to use it, there&#039;s something very bad going on. &#x2015;Tom Preston-Werner"; 
Quotation[407] = "Your best work is your expression of yourself. Now, you may not be the greatest at it, but when you do it, you&#039;re the only expert. &#x2015;Frank Gehry"; 
Quotation[408] = "You can have an art experience in front of a Rembrandt… or in front of a piece of graphic design. &#x2015;Stefan Sagmeister"; 
Quotation[409] = "Watch what people are cynical about, and one can often discover what they lack &#x2015;George Patton"; 
Quotation[410] = "Great ideas, like babies, are often conceived after a few glasses of wine. &#x2015;Sharon Moore"; 
Quotation[411] = "Problems with visual design can turn users off so quickly that they never discover all the smart choices you made with navigation or interaction design. &#x2015;Jesse James Garrett"; 
Quotation[412] = "Theory can blind observation. &#x2015;Carol Gilligan"; 
Quotation[413] = "Listen to your client, take into consideration all of their input, weigh the options, study the details, know the target audience, and then, if necessary, ignore all of it and design what you think will work best. &#x2015;Von R. Glitschka"; 
Quotation[414] = "A camel is a horse designed by a committee. &#x2015;Sir Alec Issigonis"; 
Quotation[415] = "Buy the best and you only cry once. &#x2015;Miles Redd"; 
Quotation[416] = "The enemy of art is the absence of limitations. &#x2015;Orson Welles"; 
Quotation[417] = "Just because it&#039;s simple doesn&#039;t mean it makes sense. &#x2015;Morgan Ashley"; 
Quotation[418] = "At this point in experience design&#039;s evolution, satisfaction ought to be the norm, and delight out to be the goal. &#x2015;Stephen Anderson"; 
Quotation[419] = "My eyes hurt, but my hand keeps sketching. &#x2015;Pablo del Valle"; 
Quotation[420] = "I became a graphic artist because of the tools. I love working at a big drawing table with traditional tools&#058; T-squares, compasses, mechanical pencils, French curves, blank ink, and graphite. At a computer, one works on a keyboard. I never considered myself a typist. &#x2015;Michael Schwab"; 
Quotation[421] = "There&#039;s way too much talk about CSS and XHTML and Standards and Accessibility and not enough talk about people. CSS and Standards Compliant Code are just tools – you have to know what to build with these tools. Great, I&#039;m glad your UI doesn&#039;t use tables. So what? Who cares if it still doesn&#039;t let people achieve their goals. &#x2015;Jason Fried"; 
Quotation[422] = "Calvin&#058; You can&#039;t just turn on creativity like a faucet. You have to be in the right mood. Hobbes&#058; What mood is that? Calvin&#058; Last-minute panic. &#x2015;Calvin & Hobbes"; 
Quotation[423] = "If I want to get hired to do something, I should already be doing it. &#x2015;Trent Walton"; 
Quotation[424] = "How can there be too many typefaces in the world? Are there too many songs, too many books, too many places to go? &#x2015;Rian Hughes"; 
Quotation[425] = "A well-defined problem is half solved. &#x2015;Michael Osborne"; 
Quotation[426] = "The secret of success is doing something you love, doing it well and being recognized for it. &#x2015;George Carlin"; 
Quotation[427] = "Most companies are looking to &#034;wow&#034; with their products, when in reality what they should be looking for is an &#034;of course&#034; reaction from their users. &#x2015;Christian Lindholm"; 
Quotation[428] = "Create your own visual style… let it be unique for yourself and yet identifiable for others. &#x2015;Orson Welles"; 
Quotation[429] = "When is the last time you saw a Lamborghini sale? &#x2015;Chris Campbell"; 
Quotation[430] = "I want to risk hitting my head on the ceiling of my talent. I want to really test it out and say&#058; O.K., you&#039;re not that good. You just reached the level here. I don&#039;t ever want to fail, but I want to risk failure every time out of the gate. &#x2015;Quentin Tarantino"; 
Quotation[431] = "The difference between a Designer and Developer, when it comes to design skills, is the difference between shooting a bullet and throwing it. &#x2015;Scott Hanselman"; 
Quotation[432] = "Don&#039;t spend too much time planning, release early and often, some things will work, others won&#039;t, refine and move forward and above all forget the money, just make sure you love what you&#039;re doing. &#x2015;Kevin Rose"; 
Quotation[433] = "Designing something is like having a baby. Asking me to try another design once I&#039;ve birthed something amazing is like asking me to put the baby back in the womb and try again. That never works out for anyone. &#x2015;Chad McMillan"; 
Quotation[434] = "Stop downloading. Start uploading. &#x2015;Jay Bradner"; 
Quotation[435] = "The inventors will invent, for that is what inventors do. The technology will come first, the products second, and then the needs will slowly appear, as new applications become luxuries, then &#034;needs,&#034; and finally, essential. &#x2015;Don Norman"; 
Quotation[436] = "Interesting things never happen to me. I happen to them. &#x2015;Bernard Shaw"; 
Quotation[437] = "Simply making decisions, one after another, can be a form of art. &#x2015;John Gruber"; 
Quotation[438] = "Creating something out of thin air is easy. It&#039;s finding the air that&#039;s hard. &#x2015;Asher Trotter"; 
Quotation[439] = "It&#039;s quicker to hate on a design picking out all the little things that should have done than to just do something great yourself. &#x2015;Tom Watson"; 
Quotation[440] = "The grid system is an aid, not a guarantee. It permits a number of possible uses and each designer can look for a solution appropriate to his personal style. But one must learn how to use the grid; it is an art that requires practice. &#x2015;Josef Muller-Brockmann"; 
Quotation[441] = "The control which designers know in the print medium, and often desire in the web medium, is simply a function of the limitation of the printed page. We should embrace the fact that the web doesn&#039;t have the same constraints, and design for this flexibility. But first, we must &#034;accept the ebb and flow of things.&#034; &#x2015;John Allsopp"; 
Quotation[442] = "Design is a plan for arranging elements in such a way as best to accomplish a particular purpose. &#x2015;Charles Eames"; 
Quotation[443] = "No masterpiece was ever created by a lazy artist. &#x2015;Salvador Dali"; 
Quotation[444] = "I am. &#x2015;Robert Brownjohn (when asked What is graphic design?)"; 
Quotation[445] = "We are interpreters – not merely translators between sender and receiver. What we say and how we say it makes a difference. If we want to speak to people, we need to know their language. In order to design for understanding, we need to understand design. &#x2015;Erik Spiekermann"; 
Quotation[446] = "Be fluid. Treat each project differently. Be water, man. The best style is no style. Because styles can be figured out. And when you have no style they can&#039;t figure you out. &#x2015;Jay-Z"; 
Quotation[447] = "I make solutions nobody wants to problems that don&#039;t exist. &#x2015;Alvin Lustig"; 
Quotation[448] = "If you never venture outside the box, you will probably not be creative. But if you never get inside the box, you will certainly be stupid. &#x2015;Christopher Peterson"; 
Quotation[449] = "Education is not the answer to the question. Education is the means to the answer to all questions. &#x2015;William Allin"; 
Quotation[450] = "By far the dominant reason for not releasing sooner was a reluctance to trade the dream of success for the reality of feedback. &#x2015;Kent Beck"; 
Quotation[451] = "Everybody is a user experience designer. &#x2015;Whitney Hess"; 
Quotation[452] = "Copying one person is stealing. Copying ten is research. &#x2015;Chet Atkins"; 
Quotation[453] = "The grid system is an aid, not a guarantee. &#x2015;Josef Muller-Brockmann"; 
Quotation[454] = "Good design begins with honesty, asks tough questions, comes from collaboration and from trusting your intuition. &#x2015;Freeman Thomas"; 
Quotation[455] = "It rarely takes more than a page to recognize that you&#039;re in the presence of someone who can write, but it only takes a sentence to know you&#039;re dealing with someone who can&#039;t. &#x2015;Josh Olson"; 
Quotation[456] = "If you want to set off and go develop some grand new thing, you don&#039;t need millions of dollars of capitalization. You need enough pizza and Diet Coke to stick in your refrigerator, a cheap PC to work on and the dedication to go through with it. &#x2015;John Carmack"; 
Quotation[457] = "Design is not about innovation. Design is about communication. Innovation in design is usually a wonderful byproduct or direct result of a particular need. Design that seeks to foremost be innovative will commonly fall apart under its own stylistic girth. &#x2015;Jason Santa Maria"; 
Quotation[458] = "The major difference between a thing that might go wrong and a thing that cannot possibly go wrong is that when a thing that cannot possibly go wrong goes wrong it usually turns out to be impossible to get at or repair. &#x2015;Douglas Adams"; 
Quotation[459] = "Web design is responsive design. Responsive web design is web design, done right. &#x2015;Andy Clarke"; 
Quotation[460] = "If it&#039;s a good idea and it gets you excited, try it, and if it bursts into flames, that&#039;s going to be exciting too. People always ask, ‘What is your greatest failure?&#039; I always have the same answer—We&#039;re working on it right now, it&#039;s gonna be awesome! &#x2015;Jim Coudal"; 
Quotation[461] = "I&#039;d rather have a bottle in front of me than a frontal lobotomy. &#x2015;Dorothy Parker"; 
Quotation[462] = "Getting addicted to design is bad for design. &#x2015;Andy Altmann"; 
Quotation[463] = "I hear and I forget. I see and I remember. I do and I understand. &#x2015;Confucius"; 
Quotation[464] = "People think that design is styling. Design is not style. It&#039;s not about giving shape to the shell and not giving a damn about the guts. Good design is a renaissance attitude that combines technology, cognitive science, human need, and beauty to produce something that the world didn&#039;t know it was missing. &#x2015;Paola Antonelli"; 
Quotation[465] = "One of the tragedies of the design scene is that it always acts too late. &#x2015;Hans-Redolf Lutz"; 
Quotation[466] = "Do, or do not. There is no &#034;try&#034;. &#x2015;Yoda"; 
Quotation[467] = "Instead of asking the user to make a choice up front, maybe we can set a smart default and see if there is high demand after launch for more customization. &#x2015;Rebecca Rolfe"; 
Quotation[468] = "The simplest way to achieve simplicity is through thoughtful reduction. &#x2015;John Maeda"; 
Quotation[469] = "Creativity is in everyone; it just manifests itself differently with each person. My CPA, for example, is one of the most creative people I know. &#x2015;Ron Miriello"; 
Quotation[470] = "To create a memorable design you need to start with a thought that&#039;s worth remembering. &#x2015;Thomas Manss"; 
Quotation[471] = "I like jumping back and forth between a few different things to let my subconscious chew on one problem while my conscious works on something else. &#x2015;Loren Brichter"; 
Quotation[472] = "You came here because we do this better than you, and part of that is letting our creatives be unproductive until they are. &#x2015;Don Draper"; 
Quotation[473] = "If you have an apple and I have an apple and we exchange apples then you and I will still each have one apple. But if you have an idea and I have an idea and we exchange these ideas, then each of us will have two ideas. &#x2015;George Bernard Shaw"; 
Quotation[474] = "Great stories happen to people who can tell them. &#x2015;Ira Glass"; 



